    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I can see this behavior may confuse some, however \"fixing\" by creating an exception in the game mechanics may not be a good idea, because it will probably lead to new bugs. Maybe an attack order could default to an attack-move order, so the unit will just move until it regains vision on the target, or attack something else? (I don't think I would prefer this over just canceling the order BTW)\n\nHowever, an attack order should never become a move order, IMO a bug that needs fixing.\n"
