    "created_at": "2017-02-14T11:47:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-02-14T11:47:50Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Move is the worst thing, but attack move is not ideal either, beacuse if you lose vision due to the yak, v2 will go closer and closer every time the yak moves away until it reaches the unit with its own vision, which is too close. If there is a group there and you aim at the arty for example, it will start moving closer, yak comes with vision, v2 will shoot the closest enemy - instead of arty, but it's less annoying then the suicide walk -, vision goes away, v2 goes closer and get killed by the group.\r\n\r\n Force attack has the problem that the v2 won't change target.\r\n\r\nMaybe a thing like if the target is lost, keep moving until the spot is in your attack range but stop instead of shooting. So when the vision comes back v2 will shoot but won't ever move closer than you intended."
