    "created_at": "2019-01-06T18:51:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-01-06T19:04:52Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I have a hunch that this is fixable using our new activity system.\r\n\r\nWhen investigating #16010 I noticed that `HeliAttack` and `MoveAdjacentTo` have special case handling, introduced in #8084, to make the unit move to the targets last known position if it disappears under the fog. If we queue these moves as child activities then we can continue to check the status of the target, and recover if it becomes visible again before the move completes.  If the unit reaches the original target location without seeing it again, then we can give finally give up as we do now."
  },
