    "created_at": "2019-01-09T19:51:58Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-01-09T19:51:58Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I tried to raise some discussion on the discord channel about this, but didn't really get far:\r\n![screenshot 2019-01-09 at 19 41 19](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/167819/50924182-c2cd2000-1446-11e9-8e53-ccf2238b748b.png)\r\n![screenshot 2019-01-09 at 19 42 03](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/167819/50924204-d1b3d280-1446-11e9-9f87-5ec290fd59ee.png)\r\n\r\nArtillery style units are a problem: they can't move to reveal the target themselves, so that means introducing an artificial delay that forces them to sit idle and wait for the target to perhaps be revealed again.  This seems like a really bad idea in the middle of a battle, and seems unlikely to be accepted as  a fix.\r\n\r\nI will be filing an issue that makes units chase their target to its last known position and reacquire the original target if it (or something else) reveals it. I believe this adequately fixes the issue here for everything but artillery, so will mark that PR to close this.\r\n\r\nIf there really is a desire to introduce attack-idling for artillery-like units then a new, more focused issue can be created to discuss that."
  },
